<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-16571] &quot;multiple versions of ant detected in path for junit&quot; printed for every junit test case spawned by &quot;ant test&quot;</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-16571</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I saw this warning for the first time after&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-16391&quot; title=&quot;Migrate dependency handling from maven-ant-tasks to resolver-ant-tasks&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-16391&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-16391&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. To be confirmed that it wasn&apos;t there with some of the previous patches.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The same warning was taken care of &#160;in&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-13232&quot; title=&quot;&amp;quot;multiple versions of ant detected in path for junit&amp;quot; printed for every junit test case spawned by &amp;quot;ant test&amp;quot;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-13232&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-13232&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Seems to me that the issue is similar but the fix will be different.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
