                            <comment id="17316682" author="michaelsembwever" created="Wed, 7 Apr 2021 21:12:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think all that is required is this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;diff --git a/build.xml b/build.xml
index dc44066b89..50e9d21d5d 100644
--- a/build.xml
+++ b/build.xml
@@ -718,7 +718,6 @@
         &amp;lt;dependency groupId=&quot;org.openjdk.jmh&quot; artifactId=&quot;jmh-core&quot; scope=&quot;test&quot;/&amp;gt;
         &amp;lt;dependency groupId=&quot;org.openjdk.jmh&quot; artifactId=&quot;jmh-generator-annprocess&quot; scope=&quot;test&quot;/&amp;gt;
         &amp;lt;dependency groupId=&quot;net.ju-n.compile-command-annotations&quot; artifactId=&quot;compile-command-annotations&quot; scope=&quot;test&quot;/&amp;gt;
-        &amp;lt;dependency groupId=&quot;org.apache.ant&quot; artifactId=&quot;ant-junit&quot; version=&quot;1.9.7&quot; scope=&quot;test&quot;/&amp;gt;
         &amp;lt;!-- adding this dependency is necessary for assertj. When updating assertj, need to also update the version of
              this that the new assertj&apos;s `assertj-parent-pom` depends on. --&amp;gt;
         &amp;lt;dependency groupId=&quot;org.junit&quot; artifactId=&quot;junit-bom&quot; type=&quot;pom&quot; scope=&quot;test&quot;/&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17316699" author="brandon.williams" created="Wed, 7 Apr 2021 21:30:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hmm, even with a little extra effort:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;diff --git a/build.xml b/build.xml
index 15f3219..2a0b7fd 100644
--- a/build.xml
+++ b/build.xml
@@ -267,15 +267,18 @@
         &amp;lt;pathelement location=&quot;${build.classes.main}&quot; /&amp;gt;
         &amp;lt;fileset dir=&quot;${build.dir.lib}&quot;&amp;gt;
             &amp;lt;include name=&quot;**/*.jar&quot; /&amp;gt;
+           &amp;lt;exclude name=&quot;**/ant-*.jar&quot;/&amp;gt;
         &amp;lt;/fileset&amp;gt;
     &amp;lt;/path&amp;gt;
     &amp;lt;path id=&quot;cassandra.classpath.test&quot;&amp;gt;
         &amp;lt;file file=&quot;${build.dir}/${final.name}.jar&quot;/&amp;gt; &amp;lt;!-- we need the jar for tests and benchmarks (multi-version jar) --&amp;gt;
         &amp;lt;fileset dir=&quot;${build.dir.lib}&quot;&amp;gt;
             &amp;lt;include name=&quot;**/*.jar&quot; /&amp;gt;
+           &amp;lt;exclude name=&quot;**/ant-*.jar&quot;/&amp;gt;
         &amp;lt;/fileset&amp;gt;
         &amp;lt;fileset dir=&quot;${test.lib}/jars&quot;&amp;gt;
             &amp;lt;include name=&quot;**/*.jar&quot; /&amp;gt;
+           &amp;lt;exclude name=&quot;**/ant-*.jar&quot;/&amp;gt;
         &amp;lt;/fileset&amp;gt;
     &amp;lt;/path&amp;gt;
 
@@ -718,7 +721,6 @@
         &amp;lt;dependency groupId=&quot;org.openjdk.jmh&quot; artifactId=&quot;jmh-core&quot; scope=&quot;test&quot;/&amp;gt;
         &amp;lt;dependency groupId=&quot;org.openjdk.jmh&quot; artifactId=&quot;jmh-generator-annprocess&quot; scope=&quot;test&quot;/&amp;gt;
         &amp;lt;dependency groupId=&quot;net.ju-n.compile-command-annotations&quot; artifactId=&quot;compile-command-annotations&quot; scope=&quot;test&quot;/&amp;gt;
-        &amp;lt;dependency groupId=&quot;org.apache.ant&quot; artifactId=&quot;ant-junit&quot; version=&quot;1.9.7&quot; scope=&quot;test&quot;/&amp;gt;
         &amp;lt;!-- adding this dependency is necessary for assertj. When updating assertj, need to also update the version of
              this that the new assertj&apos;s `assertj-parent-pom` depends on. --&amp;gt;
         &amp;lt;dependency groupId=&quot;org.junit&quot; artifactId=&quot;junit-bom&quot; type=&quot;pom&quot; scope=&quot;test&quot;/&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I still get:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;[junit-timeout] WARNING: multiple versions of ant detected in path for junit 
[junit-timeout]          jar:file:/usr/share/ant/lib/ant.jar!/org/apache/tools/ant/Project.class
[junit-timeout]      and jar:file:/home/ubuntu/cassandra/build/test/lib/jars/ant-1.9.7.jar!/org/apache/tools/ant/Project.class
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17316700" author="michaelsembwever" created="Wed, 7 Apr 2021 21:36:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=brandon.williams&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;brandon.williams&quot;&gt;brandon.williams&lt;/a&gt;, with my patch above, the file &lt;tt&gt;/home/ubuntu/cassandra/build/test/lib/jars/ant-1.9.7.jar&lt;/tt&gt; should not exist.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17316701" author="edimitrova" created="Wed, 7 Apr 2021 21:38:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have a patch... give me a few minutes &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17316708" author="edimitrova" created="Wed, 7 Apr 2021 21:41:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/ekaterinadimitrova2/cassandra/pull/104&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;PR&lt;/a&gt;&#160;| &lt;a href=&quot;https://app.circleci.com/pipelines/github/ekaterinadimitrova2/cassandra?branch=CASSANDRA-16571-trunk&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;CI&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17316709" author="edimitrova" created="Wed, 7 Apr 2021 21:42:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Locally I don&apos;t see anymore the issue, in circle too (it is still running but before the warning was before every test and we don&apos;t see it now)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17316712" author="brandon.williams" created="Wed, 7 Apr 2021 21:44:47 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Brandon Williams, with my patch above, the file /home/ubuntu/cassandra/build/test/lib/jars/ant-1.9.7.jar should not exist.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Oops, yeah, I needed to clean.  With your ant-junit removal everything is good. +1 to that over the excludes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17316717" author="edimitrova" created="Wed, 7 Apr 2021 21:52:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1, thanks &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mck&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mck&quot;&gt;mck&lt;/a&gt;, I will commit it on your name&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17316730" author="edimitrova" created="Wed, 7 Apr 2021 21:59:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/ekaterinadimitrova2/cassandra/pull/105&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Patch &lt;/a&gt; | &lt;a href=&quot;https://app.circleci.com/pipelines/github/ekaterinadimitrova2/cassandra?branch=CASSANDRA-16571&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;CI &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For completeness I will commit it on green CI&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17317013" author="michaelsembwever" created="Thu, 8 Apr 2021 09:18:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;i realised late, my patch is wrong, as it is going to break compilation in our IDEs, as we have test classes that compile against the ant libraries&#8230;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;e.g.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;rg &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;org.apache.tools.ant&quot;&lt;/span&gt; test/&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17317170" author="brandon.williams" created="Thu, 8 Apr 2021 13:02:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Doh.  +1 to Ekaterina&apos;s exclusion patch, then.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17317439" author="edimitrova" created="Thu, 8 Apr 2021 19:31:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Confirmed in Intellij, removing ant-unit is breaking the build which is not the case with the exclusion patch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/commit/e3e11686990889aabbb4b9837f4e1cb6f82ba407&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Patch &lt;/a&gt; | &lt;a href=&quot;https://app.circleci.com/pipelines/github/ekaterinadimitrova2/cassandra/761/workflows/73ef5cfd-7568-4d04-9e59-02c8ae69279f&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;CI &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17317496" author="michaelsembwever" created="Thu, 8 Apr 2021 21:21:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;two lines are not needed. otherwise +1. thanks &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=e.dimitrova&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;e.dimitrova&quot;&gt;e.dimitrova&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
